    "name": "Hemolysis prediction credibility requirement — ISO 10993-4:2017 and ASTM F1841-97(2017)",
    "description": "The CFD model shall demonstrate sufficient credibility to support regulatory submission under ISO 10993-4:2017 (Biological evaluation of medical devices — Part 4: Tests for interactions with blood) and ASTM F1841-97(2017) (Standard Practice for Assessment of Hemolysis in Continuous Flow Blood Pumps). Acceptance criterion: normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) predictions within 15% of experimental reference values; relative hemolysis index RH < 1.0 versus predicate device. Compliance assessed per ASME V&V 40-2018 credibility framework at Model Risk Level 2.",
    "standardReference": "ISO 10993-4:2017; ASTM F1841-97(2017); ASME V&V 40-2018",
    "version": "2017-baseline",
    "rationale": "Requirements established at project initiation referencing ISO 10993-4:2017 and ASTM F1841-97(2017). These documents formed the regulatory baseline at the time of protocol approval. The model and solver have since been updated to a 2026-q1 baseline incorporating revised turbulence formulations and updated blood damage scalar transport, but the governing requirement document continues to reference the 2017 standard revisions without amendment."
  },
